# ## 5. Key Insights and Conclusions
# 
# ### Insight 1: Gender Imbalance is Improving Slowly
# - Female representation has increased from 0% in early decades to about 12% in recent years
# - Physics and Economics remain the most male-dominated categories
# 
# ### Insight 2: Age Patterns Vary by Field
# - Literature laureates tend to be oldest (average ~65 years)
# - Physics laureates tend to be youngest (average ~55 years)
# - This may reflect different career progression patterns
# 
# ### Insight 3: Geographic Concentration
# - United States dominates with most laureates
# - Western Europe accounts for majority of remaining laureates
# - Global South remains underrepresented
# 
# ### Insight 4: Growth in Recognition
# - Number of laureates per year has steadily increased
# - More shared prizes in recent decades suggest increased collaboration
# 
# ## 6. Recommendations
# 1. **Increase diversity efforts**: Targeted programs to support underrepresented groups
# 2. **Transparent nomination process**: Could help address geographic and gender imbalances
# 3. **Track impact**: Regular analysis of laureate demographics to measure progress
